[According to EU Commission Regulation (EC) 1266/2007, 'bluetongue
seasonally-free zone' means an epidemiological relevant geographical
area of a Member State for which, for a part of the year,
surveillance demonstrates no evidence of bluetongue virus
transmission or of adult _Culicoides_ likely to be competent
bluetongue vectors". During the seasonally vector-free period, the
requirements for exported animals are somewhat alleviated; for
details, see annex III [ "Conditions for exemption from the exit ban
referred to in Articles 7(2)(a) and 8(1)(a) of (EC) 1266/2007") as
amended in Regulation 289/2008 of Apr 2008, available at
<http://eur-lex.europa.eu/LexUriServ/site/en/oj/2007/l_283/l_28320071027en00370052.pdf>.
- Mod.AS]
